Since 2014 Diabetes UK have been delivering a pilot group peer support service
for people with Type 2 diabetes, called Type 2 Together, in six Clinical
Commissioning Group areas in the Eastern and Midlands regions.
The Type 2 Together project has given people the opportunity to learn more
about living with diabetes by sharing experiences and information with others
with the condition, in informal sessions. The pilot was a huge success,
Although the Type 2 Together project came to an end in May 2016, many Type 2
Together groups are still running in the Eastern and Midlands areas. See
